dream: I'm in a weathered house with my wife and kids, it sits on the water.  Outside, a vicious storm rages.  A helicopter circles and it has a fishing line running down and into the water.  We are somehow working with it to catch fish.  Eventually, it catches something.  We open the door and take on the wind and rain to help pull in whatever the helicopter has on its line.  My son drags in the catch.  It is a snake, like a rattle snake, wet and slimy.  My family is disgusted by it but I assure them that we should kill it and eat it.  I smash its head. dead.
interpretation:
This dream can be interpreted in several ways, but here is one possible analysis:

The weathered house symbolizes the state of your current family dynamics or relationships. It suggests that there may be some challenges or difficulties you are facing, as indicated by the raging storm outside. However, despite these challenges, you are still managing to find ways to sustain yourselves, represented by the helicopter and the fishing line.

The helicopter represents a form of assistance or help that is coming from outside, possibly indicating external support or guidance you may be receiving in your waking life. The fact that you are working together with it to catch fish suggests that you are actively taking part in finding solutions or resolutions to the problems you are facing.

When your son drags in the catch, which turns out to be a snake, like a rattle snake, it signifies a hidden threat or danger within your family or relationships. The sliminess and disgust felt by your family members symbolize their discomfort or unease with this threat.

Your desire to kill and eat the snake suggests that you are determined to confront and overcome this danger. By smashing its head, you are taking definitive action to eliminate the threat and protect yourself and your loved ones.

Overall, this dream may reflect your subconscious recognition of challenges or conflicts within your family or relationships. It also signifies your willingness to face these challenges head-on and take action to address them, ensuring the well-being and security of your family.
title: The Stormy Hunt: Battling Nature's Fury for a Surprising Catch

dream: I am in a very large open room of a cave.  A man tells me to put on a pair of his shoes, they are like keds, grey with shoelaces tied in back so that my foot fits better.  I put them on and the man goes across the room and puts a container of amber on a shelf.  He then begins to carve different things in the wet clay of the wall.
interpretation:
This dream could symbolize a sense of exploration, adaptability, and personal growth. The large open room of the cave represents the vastness of your own subconscious mind or the unexplored aspects of your life. The man in the dream could represent an inner guide or mentor figure, offering you the opportunity to step into his shoes. 

The act of putting on the man's shoes suggests the need to adapt to new situations or perspectives in your waking life. The grey color and the shoelaces tied at the back may symbolize a need for balance and practicality in your approach.

The man placing a container of amber on a shelf could represent preserving something valuable or precious in your life. Amber is often associated with clarity, preservation, and healing. This action could indicate your own efforts to protect and preserve something important to you.

The man carving different things in the wet clay of the wall may symbolize a creative process or the act of shaping and transforming aspects of your own life. It could suggest that you have the ability to mold and shape your experiences, and the freedom to express your creativity.

Overall, this dream indicates a willingness to embrace new opportunities and adapt to changes. It suggests that you have the potential for personal growth and the ability to shape your own experiences in a creative and meaningful way.
title: Caving Enigma: Mystical Encounters and Clay Carvings

dream:
I'm in this room in a building.  It's in an older section of town, where a storefront used to be.  Someone got up and a women from Alcoholics Anonymous sat down in her place.  I didn't have the heart to tell her someone else was sitting there.
Next thing I know is that I'm looking at this huge blue house from the outside with the landlord.  The building was huge and needed a lot of work. He said it had several apartments.  I said I could give him a hand siding the place but told him about my perfectionism.  The place also had these huge windows in front.
He took me to the. front and we walked up these stairs, a very narrow hallway.  The paint was very old, it was in bad shape.  Yet, he didn't think nothing of it.
interpretation:
This dream may reflect some unresolved emotions and situations in your life. The room in the older section of town suggests a sense of nostalgia or past experiences that you may still carry with you. The presence of someone from Alcoholics Anonymous could symbolize the need for support or healing in your life, particularly related to addictive behaviors or patterns.

The hesitation to tell the AA woman about someone else sitting in her place may suggest a tendency to avoid confrontation or difficulty in asserting yourself. This could imply a fear of hurting others or causing tension in your relationships.

The next part of the dream, with the big blue house and the landlord, may symbolize a desire for stability or a need to address significant aspects of your life. The fact that the house needs a lot of work suggests that there are areas in your life that require attention and improvement.

Your mention of perfectionism indicates that you may have high standards and expectations for yourself. This could sometimes hinder your progress or prevent you from taking action due to fear of not meeting those expectations.

The large windows in the front of the house may symbolize the opportunity for self-reflection and gaining new perspectives. It could also represent a desire for openness, transparency, or a need to let light into certain areas of your life.

Overall, this dream may be urging you to address past issues, seek support when needed, and find a balance between your perfectionist tendencies and taking action in order to bring positive change into your life.
title: Unexpected Encounters and a Grand Restoration: A Dream of an Abandoned Blue House

dream: I'm sitting at a table and my father is feeding me.  He didn't know that I didn't eat what he was serving but I ended up eating it, he meant well.  I'm on a bed, I'm holding my father's shotgun.  I was showing my daughter Jenny and I warned her about pointing it at me.  She ended up doing just that
interpretation:
This dream seems to symbolize various dynamics within your relationship with your father and your role as a parent. The act of your father feeding you represents care, protection, and perhaps a desire for nurturing from him. However, the fact that you didn't actually eat what he served suggests a sense of obligation or pressure to fulfill certain expectations, even if they don't align with your own desires or needs.

The second part of the dream, where you are on a bed holding your father's shotgun, could represent feelings of power, control, or protection. The shotgun can symbolize a sense of authority or the ability to defend yourself or your loved ones. Showing the shotgun to your daughter Jenny may indicate your intent to share protective measures or cautionary advice with her.

However, Jenny pointing the shotgun at you despite your warning might symbolize a sense of conflict or disregard for your guidance, potentially reflecting either challenges in your relationship with your daughter or concerns about her behavior. It may suggest a need for clearer communication or boundaries within your family dynamic.

Overall, this dream may be highlighting your desire for care and connection from your father, the responsibilities and challenges of being a parent, and the need for effective communication and boundary-setting within your family relationships.
title: "The Bittersweet Nourishment: A Father's Unintentional Care meets a Warning Shot with Jenny's Curiosity"
